This paper is about improving conversation models through the use of sentence functions. The most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and dialogue systems. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval-based and neural generative models, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) respectively.
